      %h3
        Buying a winter jumper that will last until spring

      .article-image.aspect-2-3
        -image_url = image_path("blog/winter-jumpers/red-jumper.jpg")
        =image_tag(image_url, alt: "A lady relaxes on a low stool in a dark red jumper.")
        %figcaption
          Photo by
          =link_to('Racool_studio', 'https://www.freepik.com/free-photo/beautiful-girl-red-sweater_10012768.htm')
          on Freepik

      %p
        The moment you know it's winter is the moment you realise just how much you need a good winter jumper.
        The signs start to subtly creep up on you over a few short weeks and before you know it, you are reaching for an extra layer to keep that chill off your shoulders.

      %p
        Have you checked your winter jumper collection lately?
        Are you finding that your jumper collection looks more misshapen than winter style or only fit for a Sunday couch day?
        Are you still trying to convince yourself that most of your jumpers are still okay when you know they are not?
        If this is you then read on.

      %p
        As part of my
        %span.strong
          winter wardrobe essentials
        I am getting cozy and stylish with buying winter jumpers.
        I will look at how to buy one that will stay in good shape and keep you warm all winter.

      %h3
        Top tips and essentials for warm and stylish jumpers

      %p
        Adding a new winter jumper to your current wardrobe is something you need to get right well before the winter weather kicks in.
        Do you know why?
        Because the right jumper will support you and your wardrobe all the way through to spring.
        So, it’s important to make the right choice now and be sure that any jumper that catches your eye is really up to the job.

      %p
        So how do you know if a new jumper is going to work for you and your wardrobe and not let you down mid-winter?
        Where do you start and what do you look for? 

      %h3
        How to select the best winter jumper

      %p
        Keeping you warm throughout the colder months is just the start of any jumper-buying process.
        So when should you really begin?
        As soon as you see the weather starts to change jumpers suddenly become a new focus.
        But there is a lot to live up to.
        It has to also lift your mood when it's dark and cold outside.
        It has to keep you feeling cozy and comforted whilst you spend more time inside, whilst you wait for all that winter weather to pass.

      %p
        So, is it a good idea to start early and why do you need more time to pick a good one?
        Why?
        Because, if you pick the right one, you can enjoy the cozy winter months together and you know you will feel warm and lovely in it all winter.
        Let's take a look at how to get started.

