    .article-text

      %h3
        BRANDS AND BUDGETS- HOW MUCH TO SPEND AND WHEN IT’S REALLY WORTH IT

      .article-image.aspect-4-5
        -image_url = image_path("blog/winter-jumpers/mustard-jumper-fashion.jpg")
        =image_tag(image_url, alt: "A lady wears a slim fitted mustard jumper under a zipped jacket with a pencil skirt.")
        %figcaption
          Photo by
          =link_to('javi_indy', 'https://www.freepik.com/free-photo/portrait-fashion-girl-cute-outdoors_1069659.htm')
          on Freepik

      %p
        I have left this section until last for a very good reason.
        Do you know what that reason might be?
        I felt it was important to cover the ‘cost of care’ before covering the subject of ‘brands and budget’.
        Why? Because care and ‘cost of care’, can determine which brands you might go for.

      %p
        So how does this work?
        Some brands always sell ‘easy care’ items and some brands may sell delicate items that you know are going to require more time and effort to keep clean.
        So, understanding the cost of care first was important to help you understand your brand choices and budget better for extra care if needed.
        Do you already have a favourite brand? How often do you check the care label before you buy an item from them?
        It is with every purchase?
        Is it occasionally or is it never?

      %p
        Not checking the care label before you buy a wool jumper could cost you dearly later on.
        Do you remember the item I mentioned in cost of care?
        The one that is sat at the bottom that is always sat at the bottom of the wash basket that is waiting to be washed with extra care?

      %p
        This is what can happen when you don't check the wash label first or you don't know the general care guide of your favourite brand.
        I like to use the following checklist against a brand, so I don’t get carried away and make a bad high-maintenance choice.

