      %p
        Your brand loyalty is down to your own personal taste and style.
        Budgets are also going to vary.
        So, how do you determine where to look?
        I would stick with your brand loyalty, if it constantly serves you well.
        But I would also never pass up the chance to take a look at what else is on offer.

      %p
        Brand styles can change to keep up with trends and designers also move on, as they carve out their designing career and build on their experience.
        So, don’t get stuck in a rut and always assume that a brand still stacks up for both you and your current needs.

      %p
        Life is constantly changing and so are brands.

      %p
        A good idea is to check every now and then on how your favourite brand measures up against other brands and what they are offering for a particular season.
        If you see something you like elsewhere, there is no harm in taking a closer look.

      %p
        Remember you are investing in yourself, not the brand. 


